      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_hit_detector_1a5d27da9908456967f0c2cd14b5369ca3" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void input</definition>
        <argsstring>(float z)</argsstring>
        <name>input</name>
        <param>
          <type>float</type>
          <declname>z</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function checks if sample z fullfills hit detection condition. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>z</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Acceleration raw data sample in vertical direction</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
The function increments current sample counter n_cur and set the bool variables is_above and is_below, where is_above is set to true and is_below is set to false if input sample z is higher than hit detection threshold. Variable n_high marks the first value over the threshold and the start of the time window. If a sample value is higher than threshold and there is no time window active n_high will be set to current sample counter n_cur and a new time window has been opened. Within the time window of length max_samples the function checks if there is a value below threshold. In this case hit detection condition is met and hit counter hit_cnt will be incremented by 1 and time window will be closed by setting n_high to 0. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
